FBIS3-30210 "dreeu020_k_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 CROATIA `Christmas' Cease-Fire Extended to 28 Feb LD3101104194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 0951 GMT 31 Jan 94 LD3101104194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Knin, 31 Jan (TANJUG) -- Representatives of the republic of Srpska army [VRS] and the Croatian Army yesterday signed another agreement -- with the mediation of the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] -- on the extension of the so-called Christmas cease-fire. The extended cease-fire agreement comes into effect at 0000 this evening. The warring sides signed their first cease-fire agreement -- the Christmas cease-fire -- on 17 December last year and on 13 January extended it until midnight on 31 January. The extended truce will be in effect until 28 February this year. The VRS General Staff said that both sides were prepared to resume negotiations on a general cease-fire.
